<paragraph blockId="2.[151,626,511,571]" box="[151,443,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
(
<figureCitation box="[159,267,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Figs. 
<number box="[222,267,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="6.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="5.0">5–8</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<number box="[279,352,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="21.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="17.0">17–26</number>
; 
<number box="[364,435,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="34.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="32.0">32–36</number>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,618,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[229,360,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[286,360,619,643]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18</number>
</figureCitation>
). Colour ochraceous with brown markings. Crown with pair of elliptical dark brown spots equally distant between eyes and median line. Frontoclypeus (
<figureCitation box="[855,937,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,218,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 36. Habitus, face and female genitalia of new species 27 – 31 female Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 27, 28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 29. Seventh sternite; 30, 31. Second gonapophyses; 32 – 36 female Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 32, 33. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 34. Seventh sternite; 35, 36 Second gonapophyses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242865/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[908,937,655,679]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
) with black thin line on ½ sulci posteriorly; clypellus pale brown with black apical half; genae ochraceous with dark brown, elongate spot on adjacent antennal ledges; lora pale brown. Pronotum with three markings as follows: one black line medially above the hind margin of pronotum reaching 
<number box="[399,413,766,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[423,435,766,790]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="3.0">3</number>
rd anteriorly; one pair of some triangular maculae at lateral area, touching the middle black line Mesoscutum pale brown with a pair of brown laterobasal triangular markings, scuto-scutellar suture dark brown; mesoscutellum pale brown. Forewings pale brown with veins brown. Female coloration similar to male (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,873,898]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,218,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 36. Habitus, face and female genitalia of new species 27 – 31 female Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 27, 28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 29. Seventh sternite; 30, 31. Second gonapophyses; 32 – 36 female Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 32, 33. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 34. Seventh sternite; 35, 36 Second gonapophyses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242865/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Figs. 
<number box="[222,297,874,898]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="32.5" valueMax="33.0" valueMin="32.0">32–33</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,618,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Head broadly rounded, crown more or less uniform in length. Anteclypeus exceeding facial margin (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,909,934]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,910,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Frontoclypeus broad with distinct transverse ridges and face with distinct median carina. Frontal suture extending onto vertex, terminating laterad of ocelli (
<figureCitation box="[637,723,981,1006]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[692,723,982,1006]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ocelli placed anteriorly on face, close to anterior margin of vertex than to antennal base, distance between eye and ocellus 
<date box="[910,938,1018,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<number box="[910,923,1018,1042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
to diameter of ocellus. Antennae situated somewhat at level with lower margin of eye in facial view. Scutellum 
<number box="[941,976,1054,1078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="0.9">0.9</number>
x as long as pronotum, and 
<number box="[1288,1337,1053,1078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="0.63">0.63</number>
x shorter than its width, transverse depression distinct and nearly reaching lateral margin. Pronotum 
<number box="[1169,1218,1089,1114]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="0.46">0.46</number>
x longer than broad and 
<number box="[198,233,1125,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="5.5">5.5</number>
x longer than crown (
<figureCitation box="[473,557,1125,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[526,557,1126,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). Forewing without appendix (
<figureCitation box="[902,985,1125,1150]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[954,985,1126,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="243" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,618,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,395,1161,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[519,592,1161,1186]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[577,592,1162,1186]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, with stout microsetae; caudoventral margin shallowly excavated in middle. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[613,698,1197,1222]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[669,698,1198,1222]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) in ventral view, elongate, subtriangular, not fused to valve but fused to each other along basal third, narrowing gradually towards apical 
<number box="[1001,1011,1237,1261]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1022,1036,1237,1261]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="3.0">3</number>
rd, subapical area directed outward; apex rounded; in lateral view, dorsal margin with short, scattered hairlike setae. Styles (
<figureCitation box="[1138,1259,1272,1297]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStart-1="FIGURES 9 – 16" captionStart-2="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId-0="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionStartId-1="4.[151,264,1954,1977]" captionStartId-2="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox-0="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1402,217,1905]" captionTargetBox-2="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId-0="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetId-1="figure@4.[170,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetId-2="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionTargetPageId-2="5" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." captionText-1="FIGURES 9 – 16. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 9, 10. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 11. Face; 12. Pygofer; 13, 14. Anal collar process; 15. Subgenital plate; 16. Aedeagus with style and connective." captionText-2="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/242863/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Figs. 
<number box="[1202,1259,1272,1297]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="16.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="7.0">7–25</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view well developed, outer fork rounded and short, bearing scattered setae, inner fork shorter with basal portion strongly curved and apical portion subacute. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[725,811,1344,1369]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Fig. 
<number box="[782,811,1344,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) in dorsal view, narrower anteriorly than posteriorly; posterior margin with single lobe. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[691,775,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[792,864,1380,1405]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 – 26" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[186,1398,227,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1427,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 17 – 26. Habitus, face and genitalia male Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 17, 18. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 19. Face; 20, 21. Pygofer, lateral and dorsal view; 22. Anal collar process; 23. Subgenital plate; 24. Aedeagus with connective; 25. Aedeagus, with style; 26. Connective." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242864/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
24– 
<number box="[836,864,1380,1405]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, lacking apical processes, apical margin slightly concave caudally, ventral margin with small groove in the middle; shaft in lateral view narrowed apically but broadened basally;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,618,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
gonopore subapical. Anal collar process (
<figureCitation box="[676,758,1488,1513]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Figs. 
<number box="[742,758,1488,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
; 
<number box="[774,803,1488,1512]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="22.0">22</number>
) dorsal view, well developed, forked near apex, dorsal fork shorter than ventral fork.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,618,2017]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1560,1585]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Seventh sternite (
<figureCitation box="[606,686,1560,1585]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1826,1849]" captionTargetBox="[230,1338,229,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[220,1354,195,1786]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 8. Male and female genitalia of new species 1 – 4 Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 1. Aedeagus lateral view; 2. Style; 3. Anal collar process; 4. Female, seventh sternite; 5 – 8 Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 5. Female, seventh sternite; 6. Aedeagus lateral view; 7. Style; 8. Anal collar process." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242862/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[698,727,1560,1584]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,218,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 36. Habitus, face and female genitalia of new species 27 – 31 female Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 27, 28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 29. Seventh sternite; 30, 31. Second gonapophyses; 32 – 36 female Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 32, 33. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 34. Seventh sternite; 35, 36 Second gonapophyses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242865/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">34</figureCitation>
) in ventral view with lateral angle of hind margin rounded and convex with median suboval lobe. Second valvulae (
<figureCitation box="[763,901,1596,1621]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 36" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[185,1402,218,1906]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[161,1425,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 36. Habitus, face and female genitalia of new species 27 – 31 female Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. 27, 28. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 29. Seventh sternite; 30, 31. Second gonapophyses; 32 – 36 female Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. 32, 33. Habitus, dorsal and lateral view; 34. Seventh sternite; 35, 36 Second gonapophyses." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242865/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="243">
Figs. 
<number box="[829,901,1596,1621]" pageId="2" pageNumber="243" value="35.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="35.0">35–36</number>
</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, slightly dorsally curved from base, with broadest point on apical 
