<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,433,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">Molecular analysis.</emphasis>
The results from maximum likelihood analysis of molecular data are given in 
<figureCitation box="[1347,1432,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,1365,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1353,1769]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 45. Relationships of Igerna kolasibensis sp. nov. and Igerna shillongensis sp. nov. inferred using Maximum Likelihood method based on General Time Reversible + Gamma distribution model of mitochondrial COI sequences. Codes adjacent to species names refer to Genbank accession numbers. Numbers above branches are bootstrap percentages, below branches are branch lengths." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242867/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">
Fig. 
<number box="[1401,1432,295,320]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="45.0">45</number>
</figureCitation>
. 
<collectionCode box="[151,234,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">MEGA</collectionCode>
V6.0 (
<bibRefCitation author="Tamura" box="[314,535,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Tamura, K., Stecher, G., Peterson, D., Filipski, A., &amp; Kumar, S. (2013) MEGA 6: Molecular Evolutionary Genetics Analysis version 6.0. Molecular Biology and Evolution, 30, 2725 - 2729. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1093 / molbev / mst 197" type="journal article" year="2013">
Tamura 
<emphasis box="[410,468,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[477,535,332,356]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) was used to caluculate percent sequence variation between 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1394,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shilongensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1231,1394,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">I. shilongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="249" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[262,427,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Igerna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kolasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[262,427,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">I. kolasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[438,532,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[438,532,367,392]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
for mtCOI sequences. The percent sequence variation between the two new species is at least 
<number box="[364,378,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="2.0">2</number>
% (
<bibRefCitation author="Tamura" box="[419,666,404,429]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" refString="Tamura, K. &amp; Nei, M. (1993) Estimation of the number of nucleotide substitutions in the control region of mitochondrial DNA in humans and chimpanzees. Molecular Biology and Evolution, 10, 512 - 526." type="journal article" year="1993">
Tamura &amp; Nei, 
<number box="[606,666,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Outgroups were taken from 
<collectionCode box="[1019,1086,404,428]" pageId="8" pageNumber="249">NCBI</collectionCode>
GenBank (accession numbers indicated after taxon name).
</paragraph>
